	<transcript sound="sound1"><![CDATA[You should take enough precautions while using cleaning chemicals and equipment to prevent hazards.<br /><br />Separate, colour-coded cloths and equipment should be used for raw and high-risk areas.<br /><br />After use, the cleaning equipment itself must be cleaned and dried.<br /><br />When using chemicals, you should always read the label before use and follow the manufacturer's instructions.<br /><br />Ensure that food is not exposed to risk of contamination during cleaning.<br /><br />To be effective, and avoid taint, chemicals must always be diluted correctly. Rinsing with clean water may be required.<br /><br />Do not mix different chemicals as it may produce dangerous gases or an explosion. Always purchase chemicals from reputable suppliers.<br /><br />Chemicals must always be stored separately from food and should never be emptied into unmarked or food containers, especially bottles.<br /><br />Staff must always have regard to the provision of health and safety and must wear suitable protective clothing.<br /><br />Click the icon to learn about your responsibility regarding safety while cleaning. When you have finished, click the Next button to continue.]]></transcript>
